    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="229"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                <head>229. Letter From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1"
                        >Kissinger</persName> to Egyptian Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_FI_1">Fahmy</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d229fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Records of <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1"
                            >Henry Kissinger</persName>, 1973–77, Box 15, Miscellaneous, Documents,
                        Telegrams, etc., 1975, Folder 8. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1975-09-01">September 1, 1975</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Ismail:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>This is to inform you that with respect to Syria, we have an Israeli assurance
                    that Israel will not initiate military action against Syria.</p>
                <p>Warm regards,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KHA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d229fn2">The original bears this typed signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
